    &lt;Title&gt;Outstanding in every way&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Michael Dawson&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I had an RPLND at the Chelsea hospital at the end of April.  This is a major operation and whilst I was a little apprehensive, I comforted myself with the fact that the Royal Marsden is world class and there are few places better to have the procedure.  I need not have worried at all – everything was first class from the brilliance of the surgeons through the skill of the anaesthetists to the compassion and care of the team on the wards.  Pain relief and recovery processes were excellent and at every step, I was kept engaged and involved which continued after I left hospital only 4 days after the operation.  
RMH is rightly rated “Outstanding“  and this reflects the dedication and morale of the staff.  Nobody chooses to have cancer but if you come here for treatment, do not worry – you could not be in better hands.  It is the NHS at its very best and it really delivers to meet your needs.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
